\ @brief CCER register
\ Address offset: 0x20
\ Reset value: 0x00000000
\

$00000001 constant TIM2_CCER_CC1E                                   \ CC1E: Capture/Compare 1 output enable CC1 channel configured as output: 0: Off - OC1 is not active. OC1 level is then function of MOE, OSSI, OSSR, OIS1, OIS1N and CC1NE bits. 1: On - OC1 signal is output on the corresponding output pin depending on MOE, OSSI, OSSR, OIS1, OIS1N and CC1NE bits. CC1 channel configured as input: This bit determines if a capture of the counter value can actually be done into the input capture/compare register 1 (TIMx_CCR1) or not. 0: Capture disabled 1: Capture enabled
$00000002 constant TIM2_CCER_CC1P                                   \ CC1P: Capture/Compare 1 output polarity CC1 channel configured as output: 0: OC1 active high 1: OC1 active low CC1 channel configured as input: The CC1NP/CC1P bits select the polarity of TI1FP1 for trigger or capture operations.. 00: Non-inverted/rising edge. The circuit is sensitive to TIxFP1 rising edge (capture or trigger operations in reset, external clock or trigger mode), TIxFP1 is not inverted (trigger operation in gated mode). 01: Inverted/falling edge. The circuit is sensitive to TIxFP1 falling edge (capture or trigger operations in reset, external clock or trigger mode), TIxFP1 is inverted (trigger operation in gated mode. 10: Reserved, do not use this configuration. 11: Non-inverted/both edges. The circuit is sensitive to both TIxFP1 rising and falling edges (capture or trigger operations in reset, external clock or trigger mode), TIxFP1 is not inverted (trigger operation in gated mode). Note: 1. This bit is not writable as soon as LOCK level 2 or 3 has been programmed (LOCK bits in TIMx_BDTR register). 2. On channels that have a complementary output, this bit is preloaded. If the CCPC bit is set in the TIMx_CR2 register then the CC1P active bit takes the new value from the preloaded bit only when a Commutation event is generated.
$00000008 constant TIM2_CCER_CC1NP                                  \ CC1NP: Capture/Compare 1 Complementary output Polarity. This field is not used in Blue51. Not available in IUM Note: This bit is no longer writeable as soon as LOCK level 2 or 3 has been programmed (LOCK bits in GPT_BDTR register) and CC1S='00' (the channel is configured in output).
$00000010 constant TIM2_CCER_CC2E                                   \ CC2E: Capture/Compare 2 output enable refer to CC1E description
$00000020 constant TIM2_CCER_CC2P                                   \ CC2P: Capture/Compare 2 output polarity refer to CC1P description
$00000080 constant TIM2_CCER_CC2NP                                  \ CC2NP: Capture/Compare 2 Complementary output Polarity. This field is not used in Blue51. Not available in IUM refer to CC1NP description
$00000100 constant TIM2_CCER_CC3E                                   \ CC3E: Capture/Compare 3 output enable refer to CC1E description
$00000200 constant TIM2_CCER_CC3P                                   \ CC3P: Capture/Compare 3 output polarity refer to CC1P description
$00000800 constant TIM2_CCER_CC3NP                                  \ CC3NP: Capture/Compare 3 Complementary output Polarity. This field is not used in Blue51. Not available in IUM refer to CC1NP description
$00001000 constant TIM2_CCER_CC4E                                   \ CC4E: Capture/Compare 4 output enable refer to CC1E description
$00002000 constant TIM2_CCER_CC4P                                   \ CC4P: Capture/Compare 4 output polarity refer to CC1P description
$00008000 constant TIM2_CCER_CC4NP                                  \ CC4NP: Capture/Compare 4 Complementary output Polarity. This field is not used in Blue51. Not available in IUM refer to CC1NP description


